value.value: Adult brain-intrinsic neuron with its soma in the brain, lateral to the anterior optic tubercle (Schlegel et al., 2024; Dorkenwald et al., 2024). It has postsynapses in the ipsilateral anterior optic tubercle, the ipsilateral superior medial protocerebrum, the ipsilateral superior intermediate protocerebrum and the ipsilateral inferior bridge (Schlegel et al., 2024; Dorkenwald et al., 2024). value.value: Adult neuron that receives input in the ipsilateral superior posterior slope and inferior bridge, then projects dorsally and bifurcates, arborizing in the bulbs and anterior optic tubercle (AOTU) small units of both hemispheres (Hulse et al., 2021; Tai et al., 2021). definition.value: Hulse et al. (2021) say these innervate a dorsal layer of the fan-shaped body, but only 3/4 neurons in Neuprint 1.2.1 have this and it is not shown in Tai et al. (2021).
